modules.description: Provides functions to parse and manipulate geometric shapes, including calculating areas, checking intersections, and transforming coordinates. Works with data types such as points, lines, and polygons represented as tuples and lists. Used to validate spatial relationships in simulation environments and render graphical elements accurately.

The module provides serialization, comparison, hashing, and conversion operations for values wrapped in a container type, along with utilities to manipulate and transform these values through algebraic operations and lifting functions into option and result types. It handles options and results by injecting a global context into specific cases, enabling structured handling of optional or error-prone computations and facilitating binary serialization and transformation workflows.
